<TITLE> Kodak finds errors in 2005 segment results </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW YORK, July 8 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Eastman Kodak Co said on Friday it discovered errors in segment results for 2005 in its regulatory filing last month, but added there was no impact on total results for that year. Kodak shares were down 42 cents or 1.5 percent at $27.63 on the New York Stock Exchange after the news. The photography company said it discovered the errors after it provided a filing on June 27 with comparable 2006 and 2005 statements to reflect a new segment reporting structure that it began on January 1 this year and to report its health group business, which was sold on May 1, as a discontinued operation. Kodak said it found that some cost allocations in 2005 were incorrectly reallocated when product lines were moved to different segments. But it said there was no impact on its total statement of operations for 2005 or 2006. The world's top maker of photographic film has said it is in the last year of a lengthy and costly transformation into a digital products and printing services provide
